Maybe we deserve it.

133
00:07:57.352 --> 00:08:00.688  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Punished?
Saul, they want to put us
out of business.

134
00:08:00.772 --> 00:08:02.315  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Man ]
Sir?

135
00:08:03.858 --> 00:08:06.152  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:69.06% 
What is it?

136
00:08:03.858 --> 00:08:06.152  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.23% 
Just got word
from Peter Quinn.

137
00:08:06.236 --> 00:08:08.237  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
Last piece of the puzzle.
Caracas is a go.

138
00:08:08.321 --> 00:08:11.324  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Set up a briefing.
Inform the White House.

139
00:08:11.408 --> 00:08:12.909  position:80.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.67% 
Yes, sir.

140
00:08:15.328 --> 00:08:19.582  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Portillo ] And the red light
is on, so I’ll yield the floor
back to Chairman Lockhart.

141
00:08:19.666 --> 00:08:22.251  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Ms. Mathison,
I’d like to use the time
before our first break...

142
00:08:22.335 --> 00:08:25.838  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
to get some clarification
on what the Agency knew...

143
00:08:25.922 --> 00:08:28.132  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
about Congressman Brody
and when?

144
00:08:28.216 --> 00:08:31.010  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:75.93% 
Okay with you?

145
00:08:28.216 --> 00:08:31.010  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Sure.

146
00:08:31.094 --> 00:08:32.846  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
When did you
first meet him?

147
00:08:34.973 --> 00:08:36.474  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
After his rescue
in Afghanistan.

148
00:08:36.558 --> 00:08:39.685  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
I was part of the team
that debriefed him
at Langley.

149
00:08:39.769 --> 00:08:41.771  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I’ve read those transcripts,
and it seems to me...

150
00:08:41.855 --> 00:08:45.066  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
you were the one
who was pressing the issue.

151
00:08:45.150 --> 00:08:47.485  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
Which issue is that?

152
00:08:47.569 --> 00:08:49.570  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
That he’d been turned
in captivity.

153
00:08:49.654 --> 00:08:54.784  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I was just doing my job, sir.
I was covering the bases.

154
00:08:56.244 --> 00:08:57.287  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:89.67% 
One moment.

155
00:08:58.788 --> 00:09:01.666  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Whispering ]

156
00:09:01.750 --> 00:09:04.251  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Mr. Portillo, would you mark
as D.O.J. Exhibit 2...

157
00:09:04.335 --> 00:09:08.422  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
a memorandum offering
the congressman immunity...

158
00:09:08.506 --> 00:09:12.677  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
in exchange for his help
in capturing or killing
Abu Nazir?

159
00:09:16.181 --> 00:09:18.265  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I show you D.O.J.
Exhibit 2.

160
00:09:18.349 --> 00:09:23.271  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Ms. Mathison, to your
knowledge, did the C.I.A.
have such a deal with Brody?

161
00:09:28.193 --> 00:09:30.445  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Uh, n-no, sir,
not to my knowledge.

162
00:09:31.446 --> 00:09:34.324  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
How do you explain
this document then?

163
00:09:38.161 --> 00:09:40.121  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
I can’t, sir.

164
00:09:41.247 --> 00:09:43.958  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Well, assuming he did
have immunity,

165
00:09:44.042 --> 00:09:46.211  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
can you at least tell us
immunity from what?

166
00:09:47.837 --> 00:09:51.048  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:69.06% 
I have no idea.

167
00:09:47.837 --> 00:09:51.048  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.23% 
Well, it wasn’t
overdue parking tickets.

168
00:09:51.132 --> 00:09:55.261  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
This is a Department of Justice
memorandum signed by
the attorney general himself.

169
00:09:55.345 --> 00:09:58.556  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
- I can see that.
- A victim of the very same
attack we’re investigating.

170
00:09:58.640 --> 00:10:01.100  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I can’t ask him,
so I’m asking you.

171
00:10:01.184 --> 00:10:04.520  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
At what point did the Agency
know Brody was a bad guy?

172
00:10:04.604 --> 00:10:06.689  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:79.00% 
- [ Kimball ]
Let me handle this.
- Ms. Mathison–

173
00:10:06.773 --> 00:10:09.692  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
Mr. Chairman, a worldwide
manhunt is under way
for the congressman.

174
00:10:09.776 --> 00:10:11.444  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Yeah, I think
I’m aware of that, counsel.

175
00:10:11.528 --> 00:10:14.947  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
As a condition of appearing
here today, you promised
not to compel my client...

176
00:10:15.031 --> 00:10:17.074  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:79.00% 
to give testimony
which might compromise
that effort.

177
00:10:17.158 --> 00:10:19.452  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I’m not asking her
to compromise a damn thing.

178
00:10:19.536 --> 00:10:21.954  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I’m asking her
just how cozy the C.I.A. was...

179
00:10:22.038 --> 00:10:24.540  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
with a traitor who went on
to kill 219 Americans.

180
00:10:24.624 --> 00:10:26.876  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
What if I told you
I don’t think he did it?

181
00:10:26.960 --> 00:10:29.170  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:84.33% 
- Carrie–
- Did what?

182
00:10:29.254 --> 00:10:33.799  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
Kill all those people.
I don’t think Brody knew
the bomb was in his car.

183
00:10:33.883 --> 00:10:36.594  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Whispered Chattering ]

184
00:10:40.390 --> 00:10:42.224  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Mr. Chairman, my client
would be the first...

185
00:10:42.308 --> 00:10:44.644  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
to tell you that hers
is a minority view.

186
00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:48.022  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Lockhart ]
A minority view?

187
00:10:48.106 --> 00:10:50.107  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
A minority view?
What’s she gonna say next,

188
00:10:50.191 --> 00:10:52.151  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
that we never landed
on the moon?

189
00:10:52.235 --> 00:10:54.236  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:70.50% 
I really think we’re
overdue for that break.

190
00:10:52.235 --> 00:10:54.236  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.66% 
No, I’m curious.

191
00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:55.821  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
I believe it’s our prerogative–

192
00:10:55.905 --> 00:10:59.909  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Just what is it
you’re smoking, Ms. Mathison?

193
00:11:07.250 --> 00:11:10.211  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
Okay. We’ll take
a 15-minute break.

194
00:11:10.295 --> 00:11:12.714  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
A word,
Mr. Chairman?

195
00:11:29.564 --> 00:11:31.857  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
So?

196
00:11:31.941 --> 00:11:35.402  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Sighs ]
I told him you
weren’t feeling well...

197
00:11:35.486 --> 00:11:38.322  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
and asked for
a recess until after
the holiday weekend.

198
00:11:38.406 --> 00:11:40.741  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
- What did he say?
- He gave us
until tomorrow morning.

199
00:11:40.825 --> 00:11:42.868  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
What the hell were you
thinking in there?

200
00:11:42.952 --> 00:11:45.996  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I was thinking
I just committed perjury
in front of Congress.

201
00:11:46.080 --> 00:11:48.249  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
Carrie,
we talked about this–
the suicide vest.

202
00:11:48.333 --> 00:11:51.377  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
It’s the one thing
the committee can never know.

203
00:11:51.461 --> 00:11:53.629  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
It would bury the Agency.
And please,

204
00:11:53.713 --> 00:11:56.882  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
you have to stop
making the case
for Brody in public.

205
00:11:56.966 --> 00:12:00.094  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:75.93% 
Well, he’s innocent.

206
00:11:56.966 --> 00:12:00.094  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:89.66% 
Nobody wants to hear it,

207
00:12:00.178 --> 00:12:02.555  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
and it undermines
your credibility.

208
00:12:05.266 --> 00:12:07.185  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:89.67% 
I need some air.

209
00:12:29.958 --> 00:12:31.918  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Sighs ]

210
00:12:33.878 --> 00:12:35.963  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
I had it in my hands.

211
00:12:36.047 --> 00:12:38.215  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:89.67% 
The actual memorandum?

212
00:12:38.299 --> 00:12:39.800  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Somebody leaked it
to the committee, Saul.

213
00:12:39.884 --> 00:12:41.635  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:89.67% 
Okay, Carrie.

214
00:12:41.719 --> 00:12:44.054  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:79.00% 
<i>I’ll get</i>
<i>to the bottom of it.</i>
<i>Calm down.</i>

215
00:12:44.138 --> 00:12:47.057  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Don’t tell me to calm down.
I feel like I walked
into a propeller.

216
00:12:47.141 --> 00:12:49.768  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
- <i>Well, you got out alive.</i>
- Yeah, barely.

217
00:12:49.852 --> 00:12:52.980  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
There’s about a thousand
people in this building
standing with you right now.

218
00:12:53.064 --> 00:12:56.400  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
- Find the leak.
- I will. You okay otherwise?

219
00:12:56.484 --> 00:12:59.320  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
You must be kidding.
[ Scoffs ]

220
00:13:18.506 --> 00:13:21.300  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Woman ]
So today we’re gonna talk
about reentry.

221
00:13:21.384 --> 00:13:24.303  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
As you all know,
this is Dana’s last day.

222
00:13:26.222 --> 00:13:30.142  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I’d like to invite her to share
her thoughts on going home
and what that’s gonna look like.

223
00:13:30.226 --> 00:13:34.897  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Then afterwards, feel free
to contribute any constructive
ideas of your own.

224
00:13:39.902 --> 00:13:41.404  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
I don’t know.

225
00:13:42.697 --> 00:13:45.866  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
Uh, I guess
that I will try...

226
00:13:45.950 --> 00:13:50.329  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
to remember the things
that we talked about–

227
00:13:50.413 --> 00:13:52.831  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
the tools
that I learned here.

228
00:13:52.915 --> 00:13:55.793  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
- Not to mention
the tools you met here.
- [ Laughter ]

229
00:13:58.212 --> 00:14:01.465  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Woman ]
What coping mechanisms
come to mind?

230
00:14:01.549 --> 00:14:02.884  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Um–

231
00:14:05.261 --> 00:14:09.515  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
"One day at a time"
and all that.

232
00:14:09.599 --> 00:14:11.934  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
And meditation.

233
00:14:12.018 --> 00:14:13.644  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Scheduling.

234
00:14:13.728 --> 00:14:15.646  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:89.67% 
Asking for help.

235
00:14:15.730 --> 00:14:20.275  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
We talked about
really slowing things down
so they’re not so overwhelming.

236
00:14:20.359 --> 00:14:24.864  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Right. Making lists.
I wrote that down somewhere.

237
00:14:30.745 --> 00:14:32.955  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Chuckles ]

238
00:14:33.039 --> 00:14:36.959  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Okay, who else wants to share?

239
00:14:39.253 --> 00:14:42.965  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Dana has made great progress
over the last month.

240
00:14:43.049 --> 00:14:45.509  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Her eating and sleeping
patterns are normal.

241
00:14:45.593 --> 00:14:50.305  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
She participates in group.
She’s doing well.

242
00:14:50.389 --> 00:14:53.600  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
You mean for someone
who got in a bathtub
and slit her wrists?

243
00:14:53.684 --> 00:14:56.062  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
Yes, that’s what I mean.

244
00:15:02.985 --> 00:15:07.573  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
What can I expect?
Um, how closely do I
have to watch her?

245
00:15:07.657 --> 00:15:09.575  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
This isn’t
just a Dana problem.

246
00:15:09.659 --> 00:15:12.578  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
I recommend
regular counseling
for the whole family...

247
00:15:12.662 --> 00:15:15.456  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
in addition to her
follow-up treatment here.

248
00:15:15.540 --> 00:15:19.293  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
We don’t have any insurance,
or any source of income.

249
00:15:19.377 --> 00:15:23.088  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
My mother had to
reverse-mortgage her house
just to pay for this.

250
00:15:23.172 --> 00:15:25.132  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
There are
county programs.

251
00:15:25.216 --> 00:15:28.010  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
I can give you a name
at the Department of
Children and Families.

252
00:15:28.094 --> 00:15:30.763  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
What is that?
A grad student?
A volunteer?

253
00:15:30.847 --> 00:15:35.851  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
Mrs. Brody, I’m worried
that you’re losing focus
of the real issue.

254
00:15:35.935 --> 00:15:38.771  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
There’s a real issue
other than my daughter
tried to kill herself?

255
00:15:38.855 --> 00:15:41.732  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Yes.
That you missed it.

256
00:15:41.816 --> 00:15:44.985  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Dana’s gesture is the kind
that we don’t often see–

257
00:15:45.069 --> 00:15:48.947  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
clear-eyed, determined,
no substances
distorting her judgment.

258
00:15:49.031 --> 00:15:50.616  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
She meant business.

259
00:15:54.203 --> 00:15:57.331  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
She was under a ridiculous
amount of stress.

260
00:15:57.415 --> 00:16:00.542  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
We’ve had death threats,
bricks through our window.

261
00:16:00.626 --> 00:16:04.004  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I had to pull her out of school.
We’re not even welcome
in our church anymore.

262
00:16:04.088 --> 00:16:07.758  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:79.00% 
I understand.
And that stress will still
be there when she goes home.

263
00:16:07.842 --> 00:16:11.721  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
You have to address it
head-on. You can’t afford
to be in denial.

264
00:16:15.558 --> 00:16:18.144  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
Let me get you
that information.

265
00:16:23.232 --> 00:16:25.234  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Door Closes ]

266
00:16:54.722 --> 00:16:57.307  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:89.67% 
When can I see you again?

267
00:16:57.391 --> 00:17:01.019  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I don’t know.
I’m gonna be under
complete surveillance.

268
00:17:01.103 --> 00:17:04.523  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:75.93% 
Your mom?

269
00:17:01.103 --> 00:17:04.523  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.66% 
No, the F.B.I.

270
00:17:04.607 --> 00:17:07.776  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh. Right.
Shit’s for real.

271
00:17:07.860 --> 00:17:11.488  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Dana!
Your mom’s here.

272
00:17:11.572 --> 00:17:13.491  position:45.00%,start  align:start size:50.00%  line:89.67% 
Got it.

273
00:17:28.339 --> 00:17:32.802  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:75.93% 
Hey. Call me.

274
00:17:28.339 --> 00:17:32.802  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
How?

275
00:17:34.136 --> 00:17:36.138  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:75.93% 
How did you–

276
00:17:34.136 --> 00:17:36.138  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Shh.

277
00:17:40.601 --> 00:17:42.645  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Sighs ]
God.

278
00:17:49.986 --> 00:17:51.904  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Man ]
There she is!
Go, go, go!

279
00:17:51.988 --> 00:17:53.780  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:70.50% 
[ Woman ]
Mrs. Brody?

280
00:17:51.988 --> 00:17:53.780  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
Come on.

281
00:17:53.864 --> 00:17:57.075  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Mrs. Brody, why was
your daughter in the hospital?
Does she have a drug problem?

282
00:17:57.159 --> 00:17:58.744  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Isn’t it true she tried
to commit suicide?

283
00:17:58.828 --> 00:18:01.163  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
- Did you try to kill yourself
because of your father?
- Where is he now?

284
00:18:01.247 --> 00:18:02.748  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Woman ]
Do you know where he is?

285
00:18:02.832 --> 00:18:07.085  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:69.06% 
How are you feeling?

286
00:18:02.832 --> 00:18:07.085  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:84.23% 
How has that tape
affected you, Mrs. Brody?

287
00:18:07.169 --> 00:18:09.338  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:75.93% 
[ Reporters Shouting Questions ]

288
00:18:07.169 --> 00:18:09.338  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.66% 
[ Engine Starts ]

289
00:18:17.680 --> 00:18:19.307  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:89.67% 
Keep your seats.

290
00:18:23.144 --> 00:18:25.354  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
Afternoon, Mr. Director.
 
What do we got?

291
00:18:25.438 --> 00:18:27.689  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
- A window.
- How big a window?

292
00:18:27.773 --> 00:18:31.693  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
Twenty minutes,
starting tomorrow,
1950 Eastern Standard Time.

293
00:18:31.777 --> 00:18:33.862  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:89.67% 
Twenty minutes is narrow.

294
00:18:33.946 --> 00:18:36.782  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
Twenty minutes
is what we’ve got.

295
00:18:36.866 --> 00:18:39.701  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
All six targets are vulnerable
in that time frame?

296
00:18:39.785 --> 00:18:41.870  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
- Yes, sir.
- What’s your assessment?

297
00:18:41.954 --> 00:18:44.289  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
There’s a lot
of moving parts,

298
00:18:44.373 --> 00:18:47.835  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
but I don’t think we’re likely
to get an opportunity like this
again anytime soon.

299
00:18:48.919 --> 00:18:51.129  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
So the plan is to take
them all out at once?

300
00:18:51.213 --> 00:18:53.966  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
That way we get everybody
before they get a chance
to warn each other.

301
00:18:54.050 --> 00:18:57.678  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
And Brody? I’m assuming
he’s not on the kill list.

302
00:18:57.762 --> 00:18:59.388  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
We don’t know
where he is, Admiral.

303
00:18:59.472 --> 00:19:01.390  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
Is it worth waiting
until we do?

304
00:19:01.474 --> 00:19:04.268  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Brody already
knows we’re after him.
The other six don’t.

305
00:19:04.352 --> 00:19:07.396  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
The president wants closure
for the American people, Saul.

306
00:19:07.480 --> 00:19:12.234  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
As his representative here,
I’m telling you Brody’s
the poster boy for this attack.

307
00:19:12.318 --> 00:19:14.319  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
No one wants to find him
more than we do.

308
00:19:14.403 --> 00:19:17.155  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
And what about
this Iranian we’ve been
hearing so much about,

309
00:19:17.239 --> 00:19:19.157  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
the mastermind
of the operation?

310
00:19:19.241 --> 00:19:21.159  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Is he also
beyond our reach?

311
00:19:21.243 --> 00:19:23.412  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
For the time being.

312
00:19:23.496 --> 00:19:26.999  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
- Scott?
- His name is Majid Javadi.

313
00:19:27.083 --> 00:19:29.584  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
He’s a commander
with the Islamic
Revolutionary Guard Corps...

314
00:19:29.668 --> 00:19:32.254  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
and deputy minister
of its intelligence directorate.

315
00:19:32.338 --> 00:19:34.589  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
He hasn’t been seen
in public since 1994,

316
00:19:34.673 --> 00:19:36.842  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
when Mossad identified him
as the man behind the bombing...

317
00:19:36.926 --> 00:19:40.137  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
at the Jewish community center
in Buenos Aires,

318
00:19:40.221 --> 00:19:41.931  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
which killed 85 people.

319
00:19:43.307 --> 00:19:46.852  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
And he’s also directly tied
to the Mykonos assassinations...

320
00:19:46.936 --> 00:19:50.314  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
and the attacks on the
Khobar Towers in Saudi Arabia.

321
00:19:53.275 --> 00:19:57.529  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
By coincidence, the director
had some dealings with him
in Tehran in the late ’70s.

322
00:19:57.613 --> 00:20:01.867  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Back then, he worked for SAVAK.
We knew him as "The Magician."

323
00:20:01.951 --> 00:20:04.995  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
- The Magician?
- He liked to make people
disappear.

324
00:20:05.079 --> 00:20:08.540  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
So he was the shah’s man
before he was the ayatollah’s?

325
00:20:08.624 --> 00:20:11.793  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:89.67% 
Yep. Go ahead.

326
00:20:11.877 --> 00:20:15.380  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
The other six
make up the network
he put together...

327
00:20:15.464 --> 00:20:18.008  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
to plan and carry out
the attacks on Langley.

328
00:20:18.092 --> 00:20:22.054  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
This is fast work, Saul.
Impressive.

329
00:20:22.138 --> 00:20:24.056  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
Thank you, Admiral.

330
00:20:24.140 --> 00:20:26.058  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
So, do we have
a green light?

331
00:20:26.142 --> 00:20:28.144  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Do I get the president
to sign off?

332
00:20:31.480 --> 00:20:34.150  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Are we decided?

333
00:20:39.280 --> 00:20:41.282  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
We’re still deciding.

334
00:20:43.451 --> 00:20:46.536  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
You did us
no favors in there.

335
00:20:43.451 --> 00:20:46.536  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.66% 
Meaning what?

336
00:20:46.620 --> 00:20:50.290  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Meaning we can’t be seen
hand-wringing in front of
the national security adviser.

337
00:20:50.374 --> 00:20:53.251  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
We’re just trying to make
the correct call here.

338
00:20:53.335 --> 00:20:55.253  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.67% 
Then make it.

339
00:20:55.337 --> 00:20:56.546  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:89.67% 
I will.

340
00:20:56.630 --> 00:20:59.716  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:84.33% 
You brought every Agency
resource to bear...

341
00:20:59.800 --> 00:21:01.968  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
on identifying
and locating these guys.

342
00:21:02.052 --> 00:21:04.930  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
What was that for
if not this?

343
00:21:05.014 --> 00:21:09.101  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
The admiral’s right.
Javadi’s the guy
we should be chasing.

344
00:21:09.185 --> 00:21:11.978  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Scoffs ]
Nobody– not even the Israelis
know where he is.

345
00:21:12.062 --> 00:21:16.817  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
Our own analysts
believe he died
in the 2005 purges.

346
00:21:16.901 --> 00:21:18.861  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:89.67% 
He’s not dead.

347
00:21:19.945 --> 00:21:23.115  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
You know what I think?
I think you’re scared.

348
00:21:23.199 --> 00:21:27.160  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Laughs ]
Six separate ops conducted
on three different continents,

349
00:21:27.244 --> 00:21:30.455  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
an untested command-and-control
team and a short clock.

350
00:21:30.539 --> 00:21:34.126  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:84.33% 
- You heard about Carrie today?
- Yeah, I did.

351
00:21:34.210 --> 00:21:37.712  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:75.93% 
She’s blowing it.

352
00:21:34.210 --> 00:21:37.712  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.66% 
She got ambushed.

353
00:21:37.796 --> 00:21:40.382  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
It’s a distinction
without a difference.

354
00:21:42.051 --> 00:21:44.386  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Somebody’s leaking documents
to the committee.

355
00:21:45.471 --> 00:21:46.472  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Who?

356
00:21:47.723 --> 00:21:49.391  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:89.67% 
No idea.

357
00:21:49.475 --> 00:21:54.063  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
Well, what we need right now
is a big honking win
to take the pressure off.

358
00:21:55.523 --> 00:21:58.150  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Yeah. A win would be nice.

359
00:21:59.527 --> 00:22:01.904  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
Another fuck-up
would be fatal.

360
00:22:16.043 --> 00:22:20.673  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Door Opens, Closes ]

361
00:22:25.719 --> 00:22:28.180  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:75.93% 
Hey, Dad.

362
00:22:25.719 --> 00:22:28.180  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Hey.

363
00:22:28.264 --> 00:22:30.557  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
What’s this?

364
00:22:30.641 --> 00:22:33.977  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
All the places Brody
may or may not have been
in the last two months.

365
00:22:34.061 --> 00:22:35.562  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
You mean reported
sightings of him?

366
00:22:35.646 --> 00:22:37.898  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Yeah. The more
reliable ones anyway.

367
00:22:46.073 --> 00:22:48.117  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
You’re off your lithium,
aren’t you?

368
00:22:49.201 --> 00:22:51.995  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Have been
for, oh, some time.

369
00:22:52.079 --> 00:22:53.289  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:89.67% 
No!

370
00:22:59.628 --> 00:23:01.254  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
All right, I am.
But it’s all good.

371
00:23:01.338 --> 00:23:03.215  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
- I feel good.
- Really?

372
00:23:03.299 --> 00:23:06.843  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Yeah. I’m medicating
myself in other ways–
exercise, meditation.

373
00:23:06.927 --> 00:23:10.472  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:79.00% 
Tequila?
I saw the empties
in your recycle.

374
00:23:13.142 --> 00:23:16.561  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I’m following a program, Dad.
A doctor-supervised program.

375
00:23:16.645 --> 00:23:18.480  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, yeah? Where’d you
find this doctor?

376
00:23:19.690 --> 00:23:21.733  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I read about him,
for your information,

377
00:23:21.817 --> 00:23:23.443  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
in the <i>Journal of</i>
<i>Alternative Medicine.</i>

378
00:23:23.527 --> 00:23:28.240  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
And he opposes the use of drugs
for psychiatric illness why?

379
00:23:28.324 --> 00:23:31.284  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
He doesn’t oppose them per se.
He just believes
in self-reliance more.

380
00:23:31.368 --> 00:23:32.869  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh, great! Well,
you let him come get you...

381
00:23:32.953 --> 00:23:35.914  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
when you’re strapped down
on a gurney,
screaming bloody murder.

382
00:23:37.666 --> 00:23:41.086  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
Look. I’m running
six miles a day.
I’m sleeping eight hours.

383
00:23:41.170 --> 00:23:43.588  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.67% 
It’s working.

384
00:23:43.672 --> 00:23:45.841  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
You think it is.

385
00:23:48.344 --> 00:23:50.971  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
219 people
died at the C.I.A.

386
00:23:51.055 --> 00:23:54.140  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:70.50% 
I understand.
Believe me–

387
00:23:51.055 --> 00:23:54.140  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.66% 
No, Dad, you don’t.

388
00:23:54.224 --> 00:23:56.685  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:75.93% 
I let it happen.

389
00:23:54.224 --> 00:23:56.685  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
No.

390
00:23:56.769 --> 00:23:58.270  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
Yeah, I did.

391
00:24:00.731 --> 00:24:04.025  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
I wasn’t myself, Dad.
I-I was only half there.

392
00:24:04.109 --> 00:24:08.864  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Sweetheart, those people
didn’t die because
you were taking your meds.

393
00:24:11.742 --> 00:24:14.369  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
It was right
in front of my eyes,

394
00:24:14.453 --> 00:24:16.455  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
and I never
saw it coming.

395
00:24:41.230 --> 00:24:43.690  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I see the babysitters
are still here.

396
00:24:43.774 --> 00:24:45.275  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Just ignore them.

397
00:24:48.987 --> 00:24:50.489  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
Ignore them
more than that.

398
00:25:10.801 --> 00:25:13.511  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
There she is.
There’s our girl.

399
00:25:13.595 --> 00:25:16.973  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:75.93% 
Hi, Grandma.

400
00:25:13.595 --> 00:25:16.973  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:89.66% 
Oh, you look so pretty.

401
00:25:17.057 --> 00:25:20.268  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:70.50% 
And so skinny. Did they
feed you in there?

402
00:25:17.057 --> 00:25:20.268  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Mom!

403
00:25:20.352 --> 00:25:22.937  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
They did, but it was awful.
I’ve been looking forward
to your–

404
00:25:23.021 --> 00:25:25.440  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:79.00% 
Chicken Divan.
I’m gonna make it
tomorrow night.

405
00:25:25.524 --> 00:25:26.650  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Great.

406
00:25:29.403 --> 00:25:31.613  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
- Hey, dingus.
- You are.

407
00:25:37.244 --> 00:25:40.706  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
- Holding down the fort?
- Absolutely.
Fort’s still intact.

408
00:25:45.127 --> 00:25:47.170  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
Well, I’ve got
some homework.

409
00:25:47.254 --> 00:25:50.715  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
Oh, but you just got back.
I thought we’d
go out and celebrate.

410
00:25:50.799 --> 00:25:53.343  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Tell that to Beowulf,
Grandma.

411
00:25:53.427 --> 00:25:56.388  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Chuckles ]
I don’t know
who that is.

412
00:25:56.472 --> 00:25:58.390  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Chuckling ]

413
00:26:17.451 --> 00:26:19.077  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
You had the bathroom redone?

414
00:26:27.503 --> 00:26:29.087  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:89.67% 
It looks nice.

415
00:27:56.633 --> 00:27:59.094  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:89.67% 
"Dear Shiva the Destroyer."

416
00:28:16.278 --> 00:28:18.780  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Paper Crumpling ]

417
00:28:51.021 --> 00:28:52.522  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Shutter Clicks ]

418
00:28:54.900 --> 00:28:56.485  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Phone Swishes ]

419
00:28:59.321 --> 00:29:01.198  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Saul ]
I didn’t want the job.

420
00:29:02.741 --> 00:29:04.743  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
I never asked
for the job.

421
00:29:06.954 --> 00:29:09.748  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
I’m not temperamentally
suited to it.

422
00:29:11.625 --> 00:29:13.543  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Who are you
trying to convince?

423
00:29:13.627 --> 00:29:14.878  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
You.

424
00:29:16.380 --> 00:29:17.881  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Me.

425
00:29:20.425 --> 00:29:21.927  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.67% 
I don’t know.

426
00:29:24.179 --> 00:29:26.681  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I hate seeing you
like this.

427
00:29:26.765 --> 00:29:28.684  position:80.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Sighs ]

428
00:29:30.811 --> 00:29:35.064  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
They could really do that?
Dissolve the C.I.A.?

429
00:29:35.148 --> 00:29:38.985  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Revoke our charter.
Yeah.

430
00:29:39.069 --> 00:29:40.570  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:89.67% 
Congress has that power.

431
00:29:42.030 --> 00:29:45.533  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:79.00% 
Then again,
some good old-fashioned
American justice–

432
00:29:45.617 --> 00:29:48.120  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Would go a long way
to restoring your credibility.

433
00:29:49.121 --> 00:29:50.663  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
A long way.

434
00:29:50.747 --> 00:29:52.582  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
So what’s
the downside?

435
00:29:52.666 --> 00:29:55.501  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
So far, the operation
sounds like a win-win.

436
00:29:55.585 --> 00:29:57.713  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:89.67% 
We’re not assassins, Mira.

437
00:29:58.755 --> 00:30:00.256  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
We’re spies.

438
00:30:00.340 --> 00:30:03.010  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
We don’t kill our targets
if we don’t have to.

439
00:30:04.219 --> 00:30:06.512  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
We trawl for them,
we develop them,

440
00:30:06.596 --> 00:30:10.016  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
and then we redirect them
against more important
targets.

441
00:30:10.100 --> 00:30:12.060  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:89.67% 
So do that.

442
00:30:13.186 --> 00:30:14.438  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Chuckles ]

443
00:30:19.943 --> 00:30:21.737  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Sighs ]

444
00:30:23.613 --> 00:30:25.157  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Let’s go upstairs.

445
00:30:28.618 --> 00:30:31.121  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
- You need some sleep.
- Okay.

446
00:30:46.303 --> 00:30:48.472  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
Here. Let me.

447
00:30:51.641 --> 00:30:55.479  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
You want some advice?
You’re not gonna like it.

448
00:30:59.566 --> 00:31:03.028  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
It’s been two months since
I’ve been back from Mumbai.

449
00:31:04.112 --> 00:31:05.321  position:45.00%,start  align:start size:50.00%  line:89.67% 
So?

450
00:31:05.405 --> 00:31:07.198  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
So, in two months,

451
00:31:07.282 --> 00:31:10.451  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
have we had
one real conversation
about what we’re doing?

452
00:31:10.535 --> 00:31:12.996  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
Yeah, we did.

453
00:31:18.460 --> 00:31:22.005  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
We agreed to take it
a day at a time,
see how it goes.

454
00:31:24.049 --> 00:31:26.509  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
We’re still sleeping
in separate bedrooms.

455
00:31:26.593 --> 00:31:29.554  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
I thought that’s
what you wanted.

456
00:31:26.593 --> 00:31:29.554  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:89.66% 
The point is, what do you want?

457
00:31:29.638 --> 00:31:32.474  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
You do everything you can
to avoid making a decision.

458
00:31:34.226 --> 00:31:37.270  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
I’m just waiting
for the right answer
to present itself.

459
00:31:37.354 --> 00:31:39.564  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Well, it’s paralyzing you.

460
00:31:39.648 --> 00:31:41.066  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:89.67% 
Apparently.

461
00:32:08.135 --> 00:32:10.137  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Good night, Saul.

462
00:32:13.849 --> 00:32:15.350  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:89.67% 
Good night.

463
00:32:22.315 --> 00:32:24.609  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
This is how Saul
wants to play it?

464
00:32:24.693 --> 00:32:26.569  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
It’s how we both think
it should be played.

465
00:32:26.653 --> 00:32:28.572  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
Well, he should have
asked me himself.

466
00:32:30.365 --> 00:32:33.285  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Chattering ]

467
00:32:36.329 --> 00:32:37.622  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:89.67% 
You’re late.

468
00:32:37.706 --> 00:32:40.167  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Kimball ]
My apologies,
Mr. Chairman.

469
00:32:41.835 --> 00:32:43.378  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
You realize you’re
still under oath?

470
00:32:44.588 --> 00:32:46.255  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Counsel has informed me...

471
00:32:46.339 --> 00:32:49.842  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
that you’re retracting some of
the comments you made yesterday.

472
00:32:49.926 --> 00:32:52.637  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
Let the record reflect
that the witness
has nodded her head...

473
00:32:52.721 --> 00:32:54.889  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
so as to indicate
an affirmative response.

474
00:32:54.973 --> 00:32:56.140  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:89.67% 
So ordered.

475
00:32:56.224 --> 00:33:00.019  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Too bad, Ms. Mathison.
You certainly woke us all up.

476
00:33:00.103 --> 00:33:03.648  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
What we’ll do instead
is clear up some confusion...

477
00:33:03.732 --> 00:33:07.151  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
as to your whereabouts in
the aftermath of the explosion.

478
00:33:07.235 --> 00:33:10.613  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
There are roughly 14 hours
you haven’t accounted for.

479
00:33:10.697 --> 00:33:15.118  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
She has accounted for them,
Mr. Chairman, in her written
statement to this committee.

480
00:33:15.202 --> 00:33:17.621  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Not to our satisfaction,
she hasn’t.

481
00:33:18.997 --> 00:33:20.832  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Where were you
when the bomb went off?
Let’s start there.

482
00:33:20.916 --> 00:33:23.584  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
My client stands by her
written statement, sir.

483
00:33:23.668 --> 00:33:25.795  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
- That she was
in the ladies’ room?
- Yes.

484
00:33:25.879 --> 00:33:28.381  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Where she was knocked
unconscious by the blast...

485
00:33:28.465 --> 00:33:31.342  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:70.50% 
and remained there for
the rest of the night?

486
00:33:28.465 --> 00:33:31.342  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Yes.

487
00:33:31.426 --> 00:33:33.302  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
For 14 hours?

488
00:33:33.386 --> 00:33:35.972  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
When she came to,
it took her a while
to get her bearings...

489
00:33:36.056 --> 00:33:38.391  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
and to make herself
known to first responders.

490
00:33:38.475 --> 00:33:42.687  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Well, we have testimony
which directly contradicts
that statement.

491
00:33:42.771 --> 00:33:44.814  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
What testimony
is this?

492
00:33:44.898 --> 00:33:48.109  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
People saw her
leaving the auditorium
with the congressman.

493
00:33:48.860 --> 00:33:50.361  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:89.67% 
What people are these,

494
00:33:50.445 --> 00:33:52.780  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
and why wasn’t I made aware
of it during discovery?

495
00:33:52.864 --> 00:33:57.451  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Because this isn’t a trial.
We’re on a fact-finding
mission here.

496
00:33:57.535 --> 00:34:01.038  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
Well, it’s starting to feel
more like a witch hunt,
Mr. Chairman.

497
00:34:01.122 --> 00:34:03.457  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Counsel, why is it
you’re doing all the talking,

498
00:34:03.541 --> 00:34:06.502  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
and your client is sitting there
silent as a sphinx?

499
00:34:06.586 --> 00:34:09.005  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Mr. Chairman,
members of the committee,

500
00:34:09.089 --> 00:34:12.633  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
Ms. Mathison is going
to assert her constitutional
privilege at this time...

501
00:34:12.717 --> 00:34:14.719  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
not to be a witness
against herself.

502
00:34:18.139 --> 00:34:19.641  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:84.33% 
Is that right,
Ms. Mathison?

503
00:34:20.433 --> 00:34:21.476  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Yes, sir.

504
00:34:23.144 --> 00:34:25.229  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
I thought so.

505
00:34:25.313 --> 00:34:26.982  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
You’re aware
of what this means?

506
00:34:28.483 --> 00:34:30.359  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
Fully aware.

507
00:34:30.443 --> 00:34:33.530  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Truth is, I don’t buy it.

508
00:34:36.449 --> 00:34:40.703  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I don’t buy half of what
you and your colleagues
are selling.

509
00:34:40.787 --> 00:34:44.665  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
You’re hiding something,
Ms. Mathison, and when we
find out what it is,

510
00:34:44.749 --> 00:34:47.418  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
we’re gonna put the whole
lot of you in jail.

511
00:34:47.502 --> 00:34:50.463  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
For now, all I can do
is hold you in contempt
of Congress.

512
00:34:50.547 --> 00:34:54.592  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
But make no mistake.
You are doing and have done...

513
00:34:54.676 --> 00:34:57.012  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:84.33% 
great harm
to your country.

514
00:34:58.722 --> 00:35:02.183  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Which you will pay for one day,
I promise you.

515
00:35:33.548 --> 00:35:36.343  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Could be the last order
we ever give.

516
00:35:38.053 --> 00:35:39.637  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
Yeah.

517
00:35:47.145 --> 00:35:48.646  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:89.67% 
Take ’em.

518
00:35:50.440 --> 00:35:52.400  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
Take ’em all.

519
00:36:07.540 --> 00:36:11.211  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:89.67% 
CARACAS, VENEZUELA

520
00:36:24.015 --> 00:36:25.100  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:89.67% 
Thank you.

521
00:36:33.441 --> 00:36:36.319  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Engine Starts ]

522
00:36:51.835 --> 00:36:54.963  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>♪♪ [ Latin Pop ]</i>

523
00:37:09.936 --> 00:37:11.980  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Horns Honking ]

524
00:37:13.064 --> 00:37:14.524  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Honking Continues ]

525
00:37:24.075 --> 00:37:26.870  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Indistinct Chattering ]

526
00:37:43.052 --> 00:37:46.097  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
That was Central Command.
JSTARS are tracking.

527
00:37:46.181 --> 00:37:49.934  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
And we should have an image
from Global Hawk 1
up on the monitor when, Sandy?

528
00:37:50.018 --> 00:37:53.229  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Sandy ]
Any second now. There.

529
00:37:54.397 --> 00:37:56.524  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
What are we
looking at, folks?

530
00:37:54.397 --> 00:37:56.524  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
Yemen, sir.

531
00:37:56.608 --> 00:38:00.361  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
The Eastern Desert. Hold on.
We’re seven miles up.
Let’s move in.

532
00:38:02.071 --> 00:38:04.281  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Yemeni intelligence
put Sherif Meshad in that car...

533
00:38:04.365 --> 00:38:06.700  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
traveling to
an A.Q. training camp.

534
00:38:06.784 --> 00:38:10.371  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Global Hawk 1
is spinning up his Hellfires.
Wants a countdown to weapons.

535
00:38:10.455 --> 00:38:12.998  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:75.93% 
Tell him to stand by.

536
00:38:10.455 --> 00:38:12.998  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.66% 
Stand by, G.H.-1.

537
00:38:13.082 --> 00:38:14.584  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Here comes Global Hawk 3.

538
00:38:16.211 --> 00:38:17.921  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
Downtown Gaza City.

539
00:38:20.006 --> 00:38:22.967  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
I believe it’s the compound
just to the right
of the crosshairs.

540
00:38:23.801 --> 00:38:25.553  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:89.67% 
Verifying coordinates now.

541
00:38:25.637 --> 00:38:27.638  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
How come we haven’t heard
from Caracas yet?

542
00:38:27.722 --> 00:38:31.642  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Gene, see if you can get Red 5.
We should have had our first
reporting by now.

543
00:38:31.726 --> 00:38:34.603  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
- On it.
- G.H.-3 has target acquisition.

544
00:38:34.687 --> 00:38:37.064  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
Copy that.
Stand by, G.H.-3.

545
00:38:37.148 --> 00:38:38.649  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.67% 
G.H.-3, stand by.

