Come on.

682
00:49:09.697 --> 00:49:12.700  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.23% 
No, fuck you!
Fuck all of you!

683
00:49:31.093 --> 00:49:33.053  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
She’s right, you know.

684
00:49:34.096 --> 00:49:35.972  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Classic counterintelligence.

685
00:49:36.056 --> 00:49:38.141  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
I told you, I didn’t
plant that story.

686
00:49:38.225 --> 00:49:40.143  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
Well, it’s straight
from your playbook.

687
00:49:40.227 --> 00:49:44.982  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I’m not saying it wasn’t smart.
Especially if things had gone
south yesterday, as insurance.

688
00:49:47.943 --> 00:49:50.571  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:89.67% 
It wasn’t me, Saul.

689
00:49:53.115 --> 00:49:57.244  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>♪♪ [ Ethereal Pop ]</i>

690
00:50:05.252 --> 00:50:08.255  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Cell Phone Chimes ]

691
00:50:30.569 --> 00:50:32.070  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Jessica ]
I know you’re trying to help,

692
00:50:32.154 --> 00:50:35.157  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
but I feel like you
have to find a way to be
more relaxed around her.

693
00:50:35.241 --> 00:50:37.159  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:89.67% 
We all do.

694
00:50:37.243 --> 00:50:39.161  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Grandma ]
I feel like
I’m doing that.

695
00:50:39.245 --> 00:50:41.247  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Jessica ]
You aren’t.

696
00:50:42.581 --> 00:50:45.458  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
Uh, if you ask me,
you’re the one...

697
00:50:45.542 --> 00:50:47.669  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
who’s making too much
of this whole thing.

698
00:50:47.753 --> 00:50:51.006  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
Too much? Of my
daughter’s suicide?

699
00:50:51.090 --> 00:50:53.008  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
She didn’t
commit suicide.

700
00:50:53.092 --> 00:50:57.345  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Jessica ]
She tried to. Very hard.
Even the doctor said so.

701
00:50:57.429 --> 00:51:00.098  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Well, of course he did.
He’s the doctor.

702
00:51:00.182 --> 00:51:02.434  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
He’s worried
about being sued.

703
00:51:02.518 --> 00:51:06.396  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
I know about teenage girls.
I raised one.

704
00:51:06.480 --> 00:51:09.316  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
My God, Jessie,
you talked about killing
yourself once a week.

705
00:51:09.400 --> 00:51:11.860  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
I talked about it,
but I never tried it.

706
00:51:11.944 --> 00:51:14.946  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
And I’m saying, she didn’t
really mean to either.

707
00:51:15.030 --> 00:51:17.741  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
It was a cry for attention.

708
00:51:17.825 --> 00:51:21.662  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
If she really meant to kill
herself, she’d be dead.

709
00:51:44.393 --> 00:51:48.647  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Lockhart ] I hereby call
this meeting of the Senate
Intelligence Committee to order.

710
00:51:48.731 --> 00:51:51.149  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Mr. Berenson,
in accordance with
the practice of the committee,

711
00:51:51.233 --> 00:51:53.027  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
will you stand and be sworn?

712
00:51:56.905 --> 00:52:00.283  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
Do you solemnly swear
that the testimony you will
give in this proceeding...

713
00:52:00.367 --> 00:52:02.369  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
will be the truth,
the whole truth...

714
00:52:02.453 --> 00:52:04.663  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?

715
00:52:04.747 --> 00:52:06.707  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:75.00%  line:89.67% 
I do.

716
00:52:09.626 --> 00:52:12.837  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:79.00% 
I understand you have
a statement you would
like to read at this time.

717
00:52:12.921 --> 00:52:16.091  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:70.50% 
<i>[ Saul ]</i>
<i>A short one, Mr. Chairman.</i>

718
00:52:12.921 --> 00:52:16.091  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:89.66% 
<i>Very well. Please proceed.</i>

719
00:52:16.175 --> 00:52:18.093  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>Thank you, Mr. Chairman.</i>

720
00:52:18.177 --> 00:52:21.513  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>Mr. Chairman,</i>
<i>distinguished senators,</i>

721
00:52:21.597 --> 00:52:23.974  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
exactly two months ago,

722
00:52:24.058 --> 00:52:27.477  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
in the worst attack
on this nation since 9/11,

723
00:52:27.561 --> 00:52:31.940  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>the men and women of the C.I.A.</i>
<i>suffered a terrible blow.</i>

724
00:52:32.024 --> 00:52:36.736  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Yesterday, we took
a decisive step in bringing
those responsible to justice.

725
00:52:36.820 --> 00:52:40.198  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
As the president announced
from the Oval Office
this morning,

726
00:52:40.282 --> 00:52:44.202  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
American air and ground forces
in a series of six
coordinated strikes...

727
00:52:44.286 --> 00:52:46.204  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
on three separate continents...

728
00:52:46.288 --> 00:52:48.999  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
eliminated the top tier
of the terrorist network...

729
00:52:49.083 --> 00:52:51.293  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
which perpetrated
the bombing at Langley.

730
00:52:51.377 --> 00:52:54.296  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
It was a textbook operation,
Mr. Chairman,

731
00:52:54.380 --> 00:52:58.174  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
meticulously planned,
flawlessly executed.

732
00:52:58.258 --> 00:53:00.719  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
I want to congratulate
all those involved.

733
00:53:00.803 --> 00:53:03.346  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
As a result of their efforts,

734
00:53:03.430 --> 00:53:06.224  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
there’s a little less evil
in the world today.

735
00:53:06.308 --> 00:53:09.561  position:50.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:79.00% 
Thank you, Mr. Berenson.
I’m sure we’re all
grateful to you...

736
00:53:09.645 --> 00:53:11.813  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
and to our brave men
and women in uniform.

737
00:53:11.897 --> 00:53:13.857  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
Thank you,
Mr. Chairman.

738
00:53:13.941 --> 00:53:16.819  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
These were civilians
who were killed.
Am I correct?

739
00:53:17.778 --> 00:53:19.988  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
The legal term
is "enemy combatant."

740
00:53:20.072 --> 00:53:23.575  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
The point is,
they weren’t the people who
actually ordered the attack,

741
00:53:23.659 --> 00:53:26.619  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
not to take anything away
from the success of the mission.

742
00:53:26.703 --> 00:53:28.621  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Of course not.

743
00:53:28.705 --> 00:53:32.876  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
The point is, you went after
the easier targets.

744
00:53:32.960 --> 00:53:35.545  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
None of these targets
proved easy, Senator,
I can assure you.

745
00:53:35.629 --> 00:53:40.550  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
Well, then, I guess
I question your timing,
Mr. Berenson.

746
00:53:40.634 --> 00:53:42.927  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:75.93% 
My timing?

747
00:53:40.634 --> 00:53:42.927  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.66% 
Coming as it does...

748
00:53:43.011 --> 00:53:47.932  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
when the American people
have lost faith in your
ability to get things right.

749
00:53:48.016 --> 00:53:50.477  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
Frankly, it feels
convenient.

750
00:53:52.229 --> 00:53:53.938  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
And this committee
will not be distracted...

751
00:53:54.022 --> 00:53:55.983  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
from fulfilling
its purpose.

752
00:53:58.652 --> 00:54:00.945  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
Which is what exactly?

753
00:54:01.029 --> 00:54:04.658  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Apart from pointing fingers
and assigning blame.

754
00:54:08.412 --> 00:54:10.163  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Perhaps you’d care
to comment...

755
00:54:10.247 --> 00:54:12.165  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
on the article
in yesterday’s paper.

756
00:54:12.249 --> 00:54:15.251  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
<i>I don’t comment</i>
<i>on unsubstantiated reports</i>
<i>in the press.</i>

757
00:54:15.335 --> 00:54:17.837  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>But if the information</i>
<i>is correct,</i>

758
00:54:17.921 --> 00:54:21.800  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>the Agency brought the bombing</i>
<i>at Langley down on its own head.</i>

759
00:54:21.884 --> 00:54:24.594  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>The information is flawed.</i>

760
00:54:24.678 --> 00:54:28.681  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
I remind you, Mr. Berenson,
that you are under oath.

761
00:54:28.765 --> 00:54:31.434  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
The information
is flawed.

762
00:54:31.518 --> 00:54:33.896  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
Flawed in what way?

763
00:54:42.654 --> 00:54:44.573  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.67% 
Mr. Berenson?

764
00:54:48.535 --> 00:54:51.121  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:84.33% 
It wasn’t entirely
an Agency matter.

765
00:54:51.872 --> 00:54:53.331  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
What do you mean?

766
00:54:53.415 --> 00:54:56.584  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
The case officer in question...

767
00:54:56.668 --> 00:54:58.879  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
has a history
of erratic behavior.

768
00:54:59.755 --> 00:55:01.632  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>She’s unstable.</i>

769
00:55:02.466 --> 00:55:05.718  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>[ Lockhart ]</i>
<i>Unstable? How?</i>

770
00:55:05.802 --> 00:55:08.596  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>She’s been diagnosed</i>
<i>as bipolar,</i>

771
00:55:08.680 --> 00:55:13.602  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
<i>a condition she concealed</i>
<i>from her superiors</i>
<i>for more than 10 years.</i>

772
00:55:19.191 --> 00:55:21.985  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>What else did she conceal</i>
<i>from you, Mr. Berenson?</i>

773
00:55:23.320 --> 00:55:24.821  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>Did she conceal from you...</i>

774
00:55:24.905 --> 00:55:27.657  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>the fact that she was sleeping</i>
<i>with Congressman Brody?</i>

775
00:55:27.741 --> 00:55:31.911  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
<i>It was on my watch, Senator.</i>
<i>Whatever happens on my watch,</i>
<i>I take full responsibility for.</i>

776
00:55:31.995 --> 00:55:34.289  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>Answer the question, please.</i>
<i>Did she conceal from you...</i>

777
00:55:34.373 --> 00:55:38.752  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>the fact that she was sleeping</i>
<i>with Congressman Brody?</i>

778
00:55:41.088 --> 00:55:43.757  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>I’m afraid she did, yes.</i>

779
00:55:46.552 --> 00:55:50.138  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
God– God.

780
00:57:57.349 --> 00:57:58.766  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
<i>[ Crickets Chirping ]</i>

781
00:57:58.850 --> 00:58:00.268  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
<i>[ Splash ]</i>

782
00:58:02.062 --> 00:58:04.690  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:5.00% 
